Package kse.utilclass.sets

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BackstepIterator<E>  
    OperatingSet<E>  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArraySet<E>
    ArraySet is a java.util.AbstractSet which implements the package own OperatingSet interface for convenient set operations.
    SetStack<E>
    Class working as Set<E> interface but adds functionality of the Stack<E> and List<E> interfaces, in other words: adds an ordering aspect to the set of elements while at the same time can operate as a stack.
    SortedArraySet<E>
    SortedArraySet is an extension of ArraySet implementing the SortedSet interface.
